        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Blackjack Mountain, or
14 miles northeast of Wedowee, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Frolona, Blackjack Mountain, Ephesus, and Roosterville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
